Clutch - Earth Rocker  mp3  320k  a2k  2013 What we got...Earth Rocker is the tenth studio album by American rock band Clutch. It was released on March 15, 2013 by Weathermaker Music. Earth Rocker is the first studio album to be released by Clutch since Strange Cousins from the West in 2009. The album is produced by Machine, who also produced the band's 2004 album Blast Tyrant.Reception


The album met with generally favourable reviews., with About.com comparing it to Blast Tyrant and praising it for "kick(ing) harder than a mule on steroids." Metalinjection described Earth Rocker as "a consistently rocking and rolling beast. On the journey through the world of modern hard-rock, Clutch is like the mad village storyteller. You might not get what he's trying to tell you right away, but after a while you discover he's the one you should have listened to all along." However, Q Magazine criticized the album as being "business as usual" despite being "a little more concise than their usual output."
